1. Introduction

At our studio , we are committed to protecting the privacy of our users. This Privacy Policy applies to all our games listed below and describes how we collect, use, and share your personal information.

Games Covered:

Ball Crush
Cartoon Bricks
Color Bounce
Color Pass
Slide Brick(s)
Sliding Ball
Tempo Run
2. Information Collection

We collect information that you provide directly to us, such as when you create an account or contact customer support. We also automatically collect information through the use of our games, such as device information, game activity, and in some cases, location information.

3. Use of Information

The information we collect is used to operate our games effectively, to provide you with a better gaming experience, and to support our internal analytics and reporting.

4. Sharing of Information

We may share your information with third parties in the following ways:

With service providers that perform services for us.
To comply with legal obligations or to respond to legal claims.
In connection with a sale, merger, or business transfer.
5. Your Rights and Choices

You have certain rights regarding the personal information we hold about you. These may include the right to request access, correction, or deletion of your information.

6. Data Retention

We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide you with our games and for legitimate business purposes.

7. Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access or against loss, misuse, or alteration.

8. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

Our games are not directed to children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

9. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

10. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us. 

This is a basic structure and should be further tailored to match the specific practices of your company. Make sure to consult with a legal professional to ensure that your privacy policy complies with all applicable laws and regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) if you are operating in or have users in the European Union.
